  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Envelope 1: supporting access to essential health and COVID-19 response services through PHC and RCCE programs</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims at:

-	Sustaining access to primary healthcare services to the population of Zarzur community in northern Syria through Zarzur PHC center in order to provide adequate primary healthcare within the COVID-19 and health response to the IDPs and hosts in northern Idleb according to the revisited standard package of primary health care services adopted by the health cluster in Gaziantep and the IPC and case detection guidelines of the NWS COVID-19 taskforce.
-	Improving the COVID-19 response in highly affected subdistricts through innovative RCCE approaches.

Specifically, UDER proposes to:

1-	Continue providing PHC services with a focus on COVID-19 prevention, detection and referrals through Zarzour PHC!G0704018 (Idleb/ Jisr-Ash-Shugur/ Darkosh/ Zarzur). This component extends for 12 months.

2-	Implement critical components of the newly developed COVID-19 vaccine demand-generation plan by utilizing medical influencers, producing and disseminating testimonials from patients and vaccinated individuals, and using peer-influence through visible proof of vaccination in high COVID-19 affected subdistricts of Al Bab, Afrin, Idleb and Dana. This component extends for 6 months.</narrative>
  </description>
